The Confederation of African Football (CAF) has confirmed match officials for Nigeria’s 2022 Africa Cup of Nations qualifier against Benin Republic on Saturday. All the officials appointed are from Morocco. Rédouane Jiyed, 42, who became an international referee in 2009 and is one of the highest-rated referees in Africa, will be the centre referee. Jiyed will be assisted by Lahsen Azgaou (assistant referee 1), Mostafa Akarkad (assistant referee 2) and Samir Guezzaz (fourth official). The match commissioner will be Yameogo David and Ghanaian Julius Ben Emunah is the security officer. Kick off is 5pm West African Time.